The paper deals with the weight spectrum of q-ary codes associated with Grassmann varieties, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorics (cs.CO). The use of varieties associated with alternating trilinear forms suggests a connection to algebraic geometry (cs.AG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The classification problem for alternating 3-forms on (F_q)^7 involves the study of Lie algebras and Lie groups, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and geometric representation theory (cs.GR).
